Chapter on seeking forgiveness

God Almighty said: {And ask forgiveness for your sin and for the believing men and believing women}

And God Almighty said: {And ask forgiveness from God. Indeed, God is ever Forgiving, Most Merciful.}

And God Almighty said: {So glorify the praise of your Lord and ask forgiveness from Him. Indeed, He is Forgiving.}

And God Almighty said: {For those who fear God are gardens with their Lord} to the words of the Almighty, {and those who seek forgiveness at dawn}

And God Almighty said: {And whoever does evil or wrongs himself and then seeks forgiveness from God, he will find God Forgiving, Merciful}

And God Almighty said: {And God would not punish them while you were among them. And God would not punish them while they seek forgiveness.}

And God Almighty said: {And those who, when they commit an immoral act or wrong themselves, remember God and ask forgiveness for their sins. And who can forgive sins except God? And they do not persist in what they did while they know.}

The verses in this chapter are many and well known.

1869 On the authority of Al-Aghar Al-Muzani, may God be pleased with him, that the Messenger of God, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, said: “My heart is full of sorrow, and I ask God for forgiveness a hundred times a day.” Narrated by Muslim. 1870- On the authority of Abu Hurairah, may God be pleased with him, he said: I heard the Messenger of God, may God bless him and grant him peace, saying: “By God, I seek forgiveness from God and repent to Him more than seventy times a day.” Once.” Narrated by Al-Bukhari.

1871 - On the authority of him, may God be pleased with him, he said: The Messenger of God, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, said: “By the One in Whose Hand is my soul, if you had not committed a sin, God Almighty would have taken you away and brought with you a people.” They sin and ask forgiveness from God Almighty, and He forgives them.” Narrated by Muslim. 1872- On the authority of Ibn Umar, may God be pleased with them both, he said: We used to count to the Messenger of God, may God bless him and grant him peace, in one sitting a hundred times: “My Lord, forgive me, and accept my repentance, for it is You The Most Merciful. Narrated by Abu Dawud and Al-Tirmidhi, who said: An authentic hadith. 1873- On the authority of Ibn Abbas, may God be pleased with them both, he said: The Messenger of God, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, said: “Whoever is obligated to seek forgiveness, God will provide for him a way out of every distress, and a relief for him from every worry.” And He provided for him from where he did not expect.” Narrated by Abu Dawud. 1874 - On the authority of Ibn Masoud, may God be pleased with him, he said: The Messenger of God, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, said: “Whoever says: I ask forgiveness from God, who there is no god but He, the Ever-Living, the Ever-Subsisting, and I repent to Him, I will be forgiven.” His sins, even if he had fled from the battlefield.” Narrated by Abu Dawud, Al-Tirmidhi, and Al-Hakim, and he said: An authentic hadith according to the conditions of Al-Bukhari and Muslim. 1875- On the authority of Shaddad bin Aws, may God be pleased with him, on the authority of the Prophet, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, he said: “The master of seeking forgiveness is when the servant says: Oh God, you are my Lord, there is no god but You, you created me.” I am Your servant, and I abide by Your covenant and promise as much as I can. I seek refuge in You from the evil of what I have done. I acknowledge Your grace upon me, and I acknowledge my sin, so forgive me. For no one forgives sins except you. Whoever says it during the day, being certain of it, and dies that day before evening, will be one of the people of Paradise, and whoever says it during the night, being certain of it, will die before If he wakes up in the morning, he is one of the people of Paradise.” Narrated by Al-Bukhari.

“Abu”: a vowel with a ba’, followed by a waw and a hamza, which means: I acknowledge and confess. 1876 - On the authority of Thawban, may God be pleased with him, he said: Whenever the Messenger of God, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, finished his prayer, he would ask God for forgiveness three times and say: “O God, you are peace, and from you is peace. Blessed are you, O Majesty and Honor.” Al-Awza’i, one of his narrators, was asked: How to ask for forgiveness? He said: He says: I ask forgiveness from God, I ask forgiveness from God. Narrated by Muslim.

1877- On the authority of Aisha, may God be pleased with her, she said: The Messenger of God, may God bless him and grant him peace, used to often say before his death: “Glory be to God and praise be to Him. I ask forgiveness from God and repent to Him.” Agreed upon.

1878- On the authority of Anas, may God be pleased with him, he said: I heard the Messenger of God, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, saying: “God Almighty said: O son of Adam, as long as you call upon Me and hope in Me, I will forgive you for what you did.” And I don't care, O son of Adam, if your sins reached the clouds of the sky and then you asked for My forgiveness, I would forgive you, and I would not care. O son of Adam, if you brought to Me an earth’s worth of sins and then met Me, do not associate with Me anything, I will bring you forgiveness nearly as great as it.” Narrated by Al-Tirmidhi and said: A good hadith. “The clouds of the sky” with the opening of the eye: It was said: It is the clouds, and it was said: It is what is revealed to you from it, meaning: it appeared, and “the closeness of the earth” with the ḍammah of the ḍāf, and it was narrated with its kasra, The dam is more famous, which is approximately its fullness.

1879- On the authority of Ibn Omar, may God be pleased with them both, that the Prophet, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, said: “O women, give alms and ask for forgiveness often. For I have seen that you are the majority of the people of Hell. A woman among them said: Why are we the majority of the people of Hell? He said: “You curse a lot, and you are ungrateful to your spouse. I have never seen women deficient in reason and religion more likely than those of a kind heart than you.” She said: What is the lack of reason and religion? He said: “The testimony of two women is the same as the testimony of a man, and you will go days without praying.” Narrated by Muslim. Chapter on explaining what God Almighty has prepared for the believers in Paradise

God Almighty said: {Indeed, the righteous will be in gardens and springs. They will enter them in peace, secure, and We will remove whatever hatred is in their breasts. They will be brothers on beds facing each other, in which no calamity will touch them, and they will not be able to get out of it.}

And God Almighty said: {O servants, there is no fear upon you today nor will you grieve. Those who believe in Our verses and are Muslims, enter Paradise, you and your wives, and you will be filled with gold. They will be circumambulated with plates of gold and cups, and in it will be whatever souls desire and eyes will delight in, and you will abide therein forever. And that is Paradise which you were given as an inheritance because of what you used to do. Therein you will have plenty of fruit, of which you may eat.} 

And God Almighty said: {Indeed, the righteous will be in a trustworthy station, in gardens and springs. They will be clothed with silk and brocade facing each other. Likewise, We have married them to lakes of spring, in which they will pray for every fruit in security. They will not taste therein death except the first death. And protect them from the torment of hell, a bounty from your Lord. That is the great victory}

And God Almighty said: {Indeed, the righteous are in bliss. They are on couches looking on, and you can recognize the glow of bliss on their faces. They are given to drink of sealed nectar, the end of which is musk. And in that, let the competitors compete, and its setting is from Tasnim, a spring from which those who are close to you drink.}

The verses in this chapter are many and well known. 1880 - On the authority of Jabir, may God be pleased with him, he said: The Messenger of God, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, said: “The people of Paradise will eat and drink therein, and they will not defecate, nor will they excrete themselves, nor They urinate, but their food is belch like musk. They inspire glorification and glorification, just as they inspire the soul. Narrated by Muslim. 1881- On the authority of Abu Hurairah, may God be pleased with him, he said: The Messenger of God, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, said: “God Almighty said: I have prepared for My righteous servants what no eye has seen, nor no ear. I heard, but it did not occur to the heart of man. Recite, if you wish: {But not a soul knows what has been hidden for them of comfort to eyes as a reward for what they used to do} [Al-Sajdah: 17] Agreed upon. 1882- On his authority, he said: The Messenger of God, may God bless him and grant him peace, said: “The first group to enter Paradise will be in the image of the moon on the night of a full moon.” Then those who follow them are the brightest shining star in the sky: they do not urinate, they do not defecate, they do not urinate, and they do not urinate. Their combs are of gold, their fragrance is musk, and their censers are of aloe and fragrant oud. Their wives are of the virgin, of the creation of one man, in the image of their father, Adam Stone. An arm in the sky.” Agreed upon.

And in a narration by Al-Bukhari and Muslim: Their vessels contain gold, and their fragrance is musk, and each one of them has two wives whose stems can be seen from behind the flesh of beauty, no There will be no disagreement between them, and there will be no hatred between them: their hearts are the heart of one man. They glorify God morning and evening.”

His saying: “On the creation of one man” was narrated by some of them with the kha’ opened and the lam sikan, and some of them with a dhammah with both of them, and both are authentic.

1883- On the authority of Al-Mughirah bin Shu’bah, may God be pleased with him, on the authority of the Messenger of God, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, he said: “Moses, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, asked his Lord, what is the closest to the people of Paradise? Status? He said: He is a man who comes after the people of Paradise have been admitted to Paradise, and it is said to him: Enter Paradise. He says: Oh Lord, how did the people come down to their homes and take their belongings? It will be said to him: Would you be satisfied to have the kingdom of one of the kings of the world? So he says: I am satisfied, Lord. He says: This is for you, and the like of it, and the like of it, and the like of it. Then he says in the fifth: I am satisfied, Lord. Then he says: This is for you and ten. People like him, and you have whatever your soul desires and what pleases your eye. So he says: I am satisfied, Lord. He says: My Lord, so who has the highest status among them? He said: Those are those whom I wanted. I planted their dignity with my hand and sealed it. No eye has seen, no ear has heard, and it has not entered the heart of man. Narrated by Muslim.

1884 - On the authority of Ibn Masoud, may God be pleased with him, he said: The Messenger of God, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, said: “I know the last of the people of Hell to emerge from it, and the last of the people of Paradise to enter.” Paradise. A man comes out of Hell crawling, and God Almighty says to him: Go and enter Paradise. He goes to it and imagines that it is full, so he returns, and he says: O Lord, I found it full. God Almighty says to him: Go and enter Paradise. So he goes to it, and he imagines that it is full, so he returns. He says: O Lord, I found it full, then God Almighty says to him: Go and enter Paradise. You have the equivalent of the world and ten times as much of it, or you have the equivalent of ten times the world, so he says: Are you making fun of me, or are you laughing at me while you are the king?” He said: I saw the Messenger of God, may God bless him and grant him peace, laughing until his cheeks became visible, and he was saying: “That is the lowest in status of the people of Paradise.” Agreed upon. 1885- On the authority of Abu Musa, may God be pleased with him, that the Prophet, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, said: “The believer in Paradise will have a tent of a single hollow pearl as long as it is in the sky.” Sixty miles. The believer will have family therein, the believer will walk around them and they will not see each other.”

Agreed upon: “a mile” is six thousand cubits. 1886- On the authority of Abu Saeed Al-Khudri, may God be pleased with him, on the authority of the Prophet, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, he said: “Indeed, in Paradise there is a tree under which the rider of a fast, fast tracked horse can travel for a hundred A year that does not cut it off.” Agreed upon.

It was also narrated in “Al-Sahihayn” from the narration of Abu Hurairah, may God be pleased with him, who said: “A rider travels in its shade for a hundred years, without crossing it.” 1887- And on the authority of him, on the authority of the Prophet, may God bless him and grant him peace, he said: “The people of Paradise will see the people of the chambers above them just as you see the brilliant star. The one who is far beyond the horizon, from the east or the west, due to the difference between them. They said: O Messenger of God, these are the stations of the prophets that no one else can reach? He said: “Yes, by the One in whose hand is my soul, there are men who believed in God and believed in the messengers.” Agreed upon. 1888- On the authority of Abu Hurairah, may God be pleased with him, that the Messenger of God, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, said: “The sight of a bow in Paradise is better than anything over which the sun rises or sets.” Agreed upon. On him.

1889- On the authority of Anas, may God be pleased with him, that the Messenger of God, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, said: “Indeed, in Paradise there is a market that they go to every Friday. Then the north wind blows and touches their faces and clothes, and they become more handsome and beautiful. So they return to their families, and they have increased in beauty and beauty, and their families say to them: By God, you have increased in beauty and beauty, and they say: By God, you have increased in beauty and beauty after us.” Narrated by Muslim.

1890- On the authority of Sahl bin Saad, may God be pleased with him, that the Messenger of God, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, said: “The people of Paradise will see the rooms in Paradise as you see them.” “The star in the sky.” Agreed upon. 1891- On the authority of him, may God be pleased with him, he said: I witnessed the Prophet, may God bless him and grant him peace, a session in which he described Paradise until he finished, then he said at the end of his hadith: “In it is what there is no No eye has seen, no ear has heard, and no thought has come to the heart of man. Then he recited: “Their sides shall keep away from their beds” to the Almighty’s saying: “So no soul knows what is hidden.” They have the comfort of their eyes.

Narrated by Al-Bukhari. 1892- On the authority of Abu Saeed and Abu Hurairah, may God be pleased with them, that the Messenger of God, may God bless him and grant him peace, said: “When the people of Paradise enter Paradise, a herald will call out: Indeed, it is yours to Live and never die. It is yours to be healthy and never fall ill. It is yours to grow young and never grow old. It is yours to be blessed, so never Be miserable forever.” Narrated by Muslim. 1893- On the authority of Abu Hurairah, may God be pleased with him, that the Messenger of God, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, said: “The closest place one of you will be to Paradise is that it is said to him: Make a wish, and he will make a wish.” And he wishes. So he says to him: Did you wish? He says: Yes, and he says to him: You will have what you wished for and the same for him. Narrated by Muslim. 1894 - On the authority of Abu Saeed Al-Khudri, may God be pleased with him, that the Messenger of God, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, said: “Indeed, God Almighty says to the people of Paradise: O people of Paradise, and they say: May God bless you and make you happy, and goodness is in your hands. He says: Are you satisfied? They say: Why should we not be satisfied, O Lord, when You have given us what You have not given to any of Your creation? Then He says: Shall I not give you something better than that? They say: What is better than that? Then He will say: I will bestow My pleasure upon you, and I will never be displeased with you after that.” Agreed upon.

1895- On the authority of Jarir bin Abdullah, may God be pleased with him, he said: We were with the Messenger of God, may God bless him and grant him peace, and he looked at the moon on the night of the full moon, and said: “You will see it.” Your Lord is an eye as you see this moon, and you have no doubt about seeing it. Agreed upon. 1896- On the authority of Suhaib, may God be pleased with him, that the Messenger of God, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, said: “When the people of Paradise enter Paradise, God, Blessed and Most High, will say: Do you want something that I can give you more for? They say: Didn't you make our faces white? Did you not admit us to Paradise and save us from Hell? Then the veil is removed, and they have not been given anything more beloved to them than looking at their Lord.” Narrated by Muslim. God Almighty said: {Indeed, those who believe and do righteous deeds - their Lord guides them because of their faith; beneath them rivers flow in gardens of bliss. Their supplication therein is: Glory be to You. Oh God, and their greeting therein is peace, and their last supplication is that praise be to God, Lord of the worlds} [Yunus: 9]. Praise be to God who guided us to this, and we would not have been guided had God not guided us: O God, bless our master Muhammad and the family of Muhammad, as You bless Abraham and the The family of Ibrahim. And bless Muhammad and the family of Muhammad, as You blessed Abraham and the family of Abraham. Indeed, You are Praiseworthy and Glorious.

Its author, Yahya al-Nawawi, may God forgive him, said: “I finished it on Monday, the fourteenth of the month of Ramadan, in the year six hundred and seventy in Damascus.”
